Chiron is getting ready to emerge from its retrograde journey on Dec 23, the same day as the New Moon.

In astrology, Chiron is known as the wounded healer. It represents the process of taking our wounds and turning them into portals of power, wisdom, and healing.

Chiron retrograde is a very subtle energy. But when we connect with it, it allows us to reflect on our wounds and how they have helped us to grow. Its energy reminds us that our toughest experiences are there to help us grow into the best version of ourselves.

If you are moving through a challenging chapter right now, ask yourself- how is this helping me to step into the best version of myself? What wisdom have I so beautifully acquired from this situation?

A powerful reminder from Chiron too is that we can be wounded but still lead a beautiful life. 💕

Venus Retrograde reading:

During Venus retrograde, you might have thoughts of an ex or even exes coming up. It might be in dreams that you are revisiting this relationship. Or you might feel a strong urge to reach out to them. You might be romanticizing the past. Was it really that good with them? If so, why are you not together anymore? Did this person hurt you, do something unforgivable? Did you? Examine your reasons before you pick up that phone, write that text, or otherwise reach out. Especially if you (or they) are partnered. This is not the time to screw up the good life you have with your soulmate (card to the right) or screw up their life. If you need support, call a friend or family member,  someone who knew you while you were in that relationship, to help give you some guidance. It’s not time to view this previous relationship with rose-colored glasses. There’s a reason you’re not together anymore, and you might need to remind yourself what that reason is. This will pass.

Cautionary tale: Years ago, and probably during a Venus retrograde that I was not aware of at the time, I felt a strong urge to reach out to an ex. I felt like there was some unfinished business between us, and I wanted to close the chapter on a high note. I felt like I needed to apologize for some things. Well, I can tell you, I immediately regretted it. This person hadn’t changed, despite the many years that passed. He was still the know-it-all, self-absorbed person he was when I was with him. I realized I didn’t need to apologize for anything. I didn’t want anything more than to talk as adults, but he perceived it differently. He annoyed me so much. I abruptly stopped talking to him, but the whole thing could’ve been avoided if I had just checked myself. 😀

I hope this helps some of you thinking about reaching out.

Numbers; 12, 14, 1982, 7, 34, 44
